OL,6,FTonnes of hazardous asbestos has been
OL,7,Ffly-tipped in a layby near Alton.
OL,9,FEast Hampshire District Council (EHDC)
OL,10,Fofficers estimate there could be as
OL,11,Fmuch as 15 tonnes of material to clear
OL,12,Ffrom the area on the A31, known as
OL,13,FJulie's layby.
OL,15,FThere are two piles of waste, each
OL,16,Fover eight feet high.
OL,18,FThe council says the clear-up is
OL,19,Fexpected to cost taxpayers more than
OL,20,F#18,000 with the final bill likely to
OL,21,Frise.
